            <title>[LUCENE-1371] Add Searcher.search(Query, int)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1371</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Now that we&apos;ve deprecated Hits (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1290&quot; title=&quot;Deprecate Hits&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1290&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), I think we should add this trivial convenience method to Searcher, which is just sugar for Searcher.search(Query, null, int) ie null filter, returning a TopDocs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This way there is a simple API for users to retrieve the top N results for a Query.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
